33bool VideoCodecInitializer::SetupCodec(const VideoEncoderConfig& config,
34 const std::vector<VideoStream>& streams,
35 VideoCodec* codec) {
36 if (config.codec_type == kVideoCodecMultiplex) {
37 VideoEncoderConfig associated_config = config.Copy();
38 associated_config.codec_type = kVideoCodecVP9;
39 if (!SetupCodec(associated_config, streams, codec)) {
40 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create stereo encoder configuration.";
41 return false;
42 }
43 codec->codecType = kVideoCodecMultiplex;
44 return true;
45 }
46
47 *codec = VideoEncoderConfigToVideoCodec(config, streams);
48 return true;
49}
50
51// TODO(sprang): Split this up and separate the codec specific parts.
52VideoCodec VideoCodecInitializer::VideoEncoderConfigToVideoCodec(
53 const VideoEncoderConfig& config,
54 const std::vector<VideoStream>& streams) {
55 static const int kEncoderMinBitrateKbps = 30;
56 RTC_DCHECK(!streams.empty());
57 RTC_DCHECK_GE(config.min_transmit_bitrate_bps, 0);
58
59 VideoCodec video_codec;
60 video_codec.codecType = config.codec_type;
61
62 switch (config.content_type) {
63 case VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kRealtimeVideo:
64 video_codec.mode = VideoCodecMode::kRealtimeVideo;
65 break;
66 case VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen:
67 video_codec.mode = VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing;
68 break;
69 }
70
71 video_codec.legacy_conference_mode =
72 config.content_type == VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen &&
73 config.legacy_conference_mode;
74
75 video_codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams =
76 static_cast<unsigned char>(streams.size());
77 video_codec.minBitrate = streams[0].min_bitrate_bps / 1000;
78 bool codec_active = false;
79 // Active configuration might not be fully copied to |streams| for SVC yet.
80 // Therefore the |config| is checked here.
81 for (const VideoStream& stream : config.simulcast_layers) {
82 if (stream.active) {
83 codec_active = true;
84 break;
85 }
86 }
87 // Set active for the entire video codec for the non simulcast case.
88 video_codec.active = codec_active;
89 if (video_codec.minBitrate < kEncoderMinBitrateKbps)
90 video_codec.minBitrate = kEncoderMinBitrateKbps;
91 video_codec.timing_frame_thresholds = {kDefaultTimingFramesDelayMs,
92 kDefaultOutlierFrameSizePercent};
93 RTC_DCHECK_LE(streams.size(), kMaxSimulcastStreams);
94
95 int max_framerate = 0;
96
97 absl::optional<std::string> scalability_mode = streams[0].scalability_mode;
98 for (size_t i = 0; i < streams.size(); ++i) {
99 SpatialLayer* sim_stream = &video_codec.simulcastStream[i];
100 RTC_DCHECK_GT(streams[i].width, 0);
101 RTC_DCHECK_GT(streams[i].height, 0);
102 RTC_DCHECK_GT(streams[i].max_framerate, 0);
103 RTC_DCHECK_GE(streams[i].min_bitrate_bps, 0);
104 RTC_DCHECK_GE(streams[i].target_bitrate_bps, streams[i].min_bitrate_bps);
105 RTC_DCHECK_GE(streams[i].max_bitrate_bps, streams[i].target_bitrate_bps);
106 RTC_DCHECK_GE(streams[i].max_qp, 0);
107
108 sim_stream->width = static_cast<uint16_t>(streams[i].width);
109 sim_stream->height = static_cast<uint16_t>(streams[i].height);
110 sim_stream->maxFramerate = streams[i].max_framerate;
111 sim_stream->minBitrate = streams[i].min_bitrate_bps / 1000;
112 sim_stream->targetBitrate = streams[i].target_bitrate_bps / 1000;
113 sim_stream->maxBitrate = streams[i].max_bitrate_bps / 1000;
114 sim_stream->qpMax = streams[i].max_qp;
115 sim_stream->numberOfTemporalLayers =
116 static_cast<unsigned char>(streams[i].num_temporal_layers.value_or(1));
117 sim_stream->active = streams[i].active;
118
119 video_codec.width =
120 std::max(video_codec.width, static_cast<uint16_t>(streams[i].width));
121 video_codec.height =
122 std::max(video_codec.height, static_cast<uint16_t>(streams[i].height));
123 video_codec.minBitrate =
124 std::min(static_cast<uint16_t>(video_codec.minBitrate),
125 static_cast<uint16_t>(streams[i].min_bitrate_bps / 1000));
126 video_codec.maxBitrate += streams[i].max_bitrate_bps / 1000;
127 video_codec.qpMax = std::max(video_codec.qpMax,
128 static_cast<unsigned int>(streams[i].max_qp));
129 max_framerate = std::max(max_framerate, streams[i].max_framerate);
130
131 if (streams[0].scalability_mode != streams[i].scalability_mode) {
132 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Inconsistent scalability modes configured.";
133 scalability_mode.reset();
134 }
135 }
136
137 if (scalability_mode.has_value()) {
138 video_codec.SetScalabilityMode(*scalability_mode);
139 }
140
141 if (video_codec.maxBitrate == 0) {
142 // Unset max bitrate -> cap to one bit per pixel.
143 video_codec.maxBitrate =
144 (video_codec.width * video_codec.height * video_codec.maxFramerate) /
145 1000;
146 }
147 if (video_codec.maxBitrate < kEncoderMinBitrateKbps)
148 video_codec.maxBitrate = kEncoderMinBitrateKbps;
149
150 video_codec.maxFramerate = max_framerate;
151 video_codec.spatialLayers[0] = {0};
152 video_codec.spatialLayers[0].width = video_codec.width;
153 video_codec.spatialLayers[0].height = video_codec.height;
154 video_codec.spatialLayers[0].maxFramerate = max_framerate;
155 video_codec.spatialLayers[0].numberOfTemporalLayers =
156 streams[0].num_temporal_layers.value_or(1);
157
158 // Set codec specific options
159 if (config.encoder_specific_settings)
160 config.encoder_specific_settings->FillEncoderSpecificSettings(&video_codec);
161
162 switch (video_codec.codecType) {
163 case kVideoCodecVP8: {
164 if (!config.encoder_specific_settings) {
165 *video_codec.VP8() = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp8Settings();
166 }
167
168 video_codec.VP8()->numberOfTemporalLayers = static_cast<unsigned char>(
169 streams.back().num_temporal_layers.value_or(
170 video_codec.VP8()->numberOfTemporalLayers));
171 RTC_DCHECK_GE(video_codec.VP8()->numberOfTemporalLayers, 1);
172 RTC_DCHECK_LE(video_codec.VP8()->numberOfTemporalLayers,
173 kMaxTemporalStreams);
174
175 break;
176 }
177 case kVideoCodecVP9: {
178 // Force the first stream to always be active.
179 video_codec.simulcastStream[0].active = codec_active;
180
181 if (!config.encoder_specific_settings) {
182 *video_codec.VP9() = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp9Settings();
183 }
184
185 video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers = static_cast<unsigned char>(
186 streams.back().num_temporal_layers.value_or(
187 video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers));
188 RTC_DCHECK_GE(video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers, 1);
189 RTC_DCHECK_LE(video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers,
190 kMaxTemporalStreams);
191
192 RTC_DCHECK(config.spatial_layers.empty() ||
193 config.spatial_layers.size() ==
194 video_codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers);
195
196 std::vector<SpatialLayer> spatial_layers;
197 if (!config.spatial_layers.empty()) {
198 // Layering is set explicitly.
199 spatial_layers = config.spatial_layers;
200 } else {
201 size_t first_active_layer = 0;
202 for (size_t spatial_idx = 0;
203 spatial_idx < config.simulcast_layers.size(); ++spatial_idx) {
204 if (config.simulcast_layers[spatial_idx].active) {
205 first_active_layer = spatial_idx;
206 break;
207 }
208 }
209
210 spatial_layers = GetSvcConfig(
211 video_codec.width, video_codec.height, video_codec.maxFramerate,
212 first_active_layer, video_codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers,
213 video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers,
214 video_codec.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing);
215
216 // If there was no request for spatial layering, don't limit bitrate
217 // of single spatial layer.
218 const bool no_spatial_layering =
219 video_codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers <= 1;
220 if (no_spatial_layering) {
221 // Use codec's bitrate limits.
222 spatial_layers.back().minBitrate = video_codec.minBitrate;
223 spatial_layers.back().targetBitrate = video_codec.maxBitrate;
224 spatial_layers.back().maxBitrate = video_codec.maxBitrate;
225 }
226
227 for (size_t spatial_idx = first_active_layer;
228 spatial_idx < config.simulcast_layers.size() &&
229 spatial_idx < spatial_layers.size() + first_active_layer;
230 ++spatial_idx) {
231 spatial_layers[spatial_idx - first_active_layer].active =
232 config.simulcast_layers[spatial_idx].active;
233 }
234 }
235
236 RTC_DCHECK(!spatial_layers.empty());
237 for (size_t i = 0; i < spatial_layers.size(); ++i) {
238 video_codec.spatialLayers[i] = spatial_layers[i];
239 }
240
241 // The top spatial layer dimensions may not be equal to the input
242 // resolution because of the rounding or explicit configuration.
243 // This difference must be propagated to the stream configuration.
244 video_codec.width = spatial_layers.back().width;
245 video_codec.height = spatial_layers.back().height;
246 video_codec.simulcastStream[0].width = spatial_layers.back().width;
247 video_codec.simulcastStream[0].height = spatial_layers.back().height;
248
249 // Update layering settings.
250 video_codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers =
251 static_cast<unsigned char>(spatial_layers.size());
252 RTC_DCHECK_GE(video_codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers, 1);
253 RTC_DCHECK_LE(video_codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers,
254 kMaxSpatialLayers);
255
256 video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers = static_cast<unsigned char>(
257 spatial_layers.back().numberOfTemporalLayers);
258 RTC_DCHECK_GE(video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers, 1);
259 RTC_DCHECK_LE(video_codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers,
260 kMaxTemporalStreams);
261
262 break;
263 }
264 case kVideoCodecAV1:
265 if (!SetAv1SvcConfig(video_codec)) {
266 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to configure svc bitrates for av1.";
267 }
268 break;
269 case kVideoCodecH264: {
270 if (!config.encoder_specific_settings)
271 *video_codec.H264() = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultH264Settings();
272 video_codec.H264()->numberOfTemporalLayers = static_cast<unsigned char>(
273 streams.back().num_temporal_layers.value_or(
274 video_codec.H264()->numberOfTemporalLayers));
275 RTC_DCHECK_GE(video_codec.H264()->numberOfTemporalLayers, 1);
276 RTC_DCHECK_LE(video_codec.H264()->numberOfTemporalLayers,
277 kMaxTemporalStreams);
278 break;
279 }
280 default:
281 // TODO(pbos): Support encoder_settings codec-agnostically.
282 RTC_DCHECK(!config.encoder_specific_settings)
283 << "Encoder-specific settings for codec type not wired up.";
284 break;
285 }
286
287 const absl::optional<DataRate> experimental_min_bitrate =
288 GetExperimentalMinVideoBitrate(video_codec.codecType);
289 if (experimental_min_bitrate) {
290 const int experimental_min_bitrate_kbps =
291 rtc::saturated_cast<int>(experimental_min_bitrate->kbps());
292 video_codec.minBitrate = experimental_min_bitrate_kbps;
293 video_codec.simulcastStream[0].minBitrate = experimental_min_bitrate_kbps;
294 if (video_codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
295 video_codec.spatialLayers[0].minBitrate = experimental_min_bitrate_kbps;
296 }
297 }
298
299 return video_codec;
300}
